GPT4 prompt/output:
Please write comprehensive instructions for creating and launching a virtual environment for Jupyter Lab on Apple M1 with an R 4.2 kernel installed
Sure, here are the step-by-step instructions for creating and launching a virtual environment for Jupyter Lab on Apple M1 with an R 4.2 kernel installed:

Open a Terminal window on your Apple M1 computer.
Install Homebrew package manager by running the following command:
/bin/bash -c "$(curl -fsSL https://raw.githubusercontent.com/Homebrew/install/HEAD/install.sh)"
Once Homebrew is installed, update it by running:
brew update
Install Miniforge, a lightweight distribution of the Conda package manager, by running:
brew install miniforge
Create a new Conda environment by running the following command, replacing myenv with the desired name of your environment:
conda create --name myenv
Activate the environment by running:
conda activate myenv
Install Jupyter Lab and the R kernel by running the following commands:
conda install -c conda-forge jupyterlab
conda install -c r r-irkernel
Verify that the R kernel has been installed by running:
jupyter kernelspec list
This should display a list of available kernels, including the R kernel.
Launch Jupyter Lab by running:
jupyter lab
This will launch Jupyter Lab in your default web browser.
Once Jupyter Lab has launched, click on the "New" dropdown menu in the top-right corner and select "R" to create a new R notebook.
You should now be able to use R 4.2 in your Jupyter Lab environment.
That's it! You have now successfully created and launched a virtual environment for Jupyter Lab on Apple M1 with an R 4.2 kernel installed.





